Why we learn JUnit framework
SDLC-->V-module--Unit Test--Integration Test--Application code deploy to QA server

Test Fixtures in JUnit
@BeforeClass    --> Runs only once in a test class--must static
@Before         --> Runs before ever test--no static
@Test           --> Actual test logical
@AfterClass     --> Runs only once in a test class--must static
@After          --> Runs after ever test--no static
@Rule           --> For example(public TestName testName=new TestName();) testName will be change global value
@Ignore         --> Refuse to run test add ignore annotation
@FixMethodOrder --> Can give order for test


